    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "t_start": 28.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "The electron's wave function must vanish at the ring boundary \u2014 it can't pass through the iron atoms. Of all the possible standing waves, only those whose pattern fits inside the ring survive. Any wave that doesn't fit cancels itself at the boundary and is forbidden.",
