      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "The radii of the bright rings are set by the circumference of the corral and the electron's wavelength. For the 7-nanometer corral, the ground-state wavelength that fits is about 14 nanometers \u2014 one half-wavelength across the diameter. That fixes where the bright peak appears.",
