      "beat_id": "B09",
      "t_start": 78.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Crommie, Lutz, and Eigler published this image in Science in 1993. It became one of the most reproduced images in quantum physics. Not because it is beautiful \u2014 though it is \u2014 but because it shows the wave function of electrons, not as math, but as a photograph.",
